import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd
from mpl_toolkits.axes_grid1 import make_axes_locatable

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    gdf = gpd.GeoDataFrame(data, geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(data.lon, data.lat))
    us_map = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))
    us_map = us_map[us_map['name'] == 'United States of America']
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    us_map.boundary.plot(ax=ax, linewidth=1)
    gdf.plot(ax=ax, marker='o', color='red', markersize=5)
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of state capitals across the US?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='state', y='lat', data=data)
    plt.title('Which state has the highest and lowest latitude?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    max_lat_state = data.loc[data['lat'].idxmax()]['state']
    min_lat_state = data.loc[data['lat'].idxmin()]['state']
    
    chart.axhline(data['lat'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest: {max_lat_state} ({data["lat"].max():.2f})')
    chart.axhline(data['lat'].min(), color='b', linestyle='--', label=f'Lowest: {min_lat_state} ({data["lat"].min():.2f})')
    
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='lon')
    plt.title('What is the average longitude of state capitals?', wrap=True)
    avg_longitude = data['lon'].mean()
    plt.axvline(avg_longitude, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Longitude: {avg_longitude:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
